Hints for wmHBattery

Generic.
--------
% wmHBattery -h

usage: wmHBattery [-e <Command>] [-p] [-l]
  [-s2 <Percent>] [-s3 <Percent>] [-s4 <Percent>] [-s5 <Percent>]
  [-bg <Colour>] [-bs <Colour>] [-be <Colour>] [-ps <Colour>] [-pe <Colour>]
  [-fs1 <Colour>] [-fs2 <Colour>] [-fs3 <Colour>] [-fs4 <Colour>] [-fs5 <Colour>]
  [-fe1 <Colour>] [-fe2 <Colour>] [-fe3 <Colour>] [-fe4 <Colour>] [-fe5 <Colour>]
  [-ba <Degrees>] [-fa <Degrees>] [-pa <Degrees>] [-h]

   -e <Command>    Command to execute via double click of mouse button 1
   -p              Show a plug symbol when charging (Default)
   -l              Show a lightning symbol when charging
   -s2 <Percent>   Percent at which to change battery fill color (Default: 10)
   -s3 <Percent>   Percent at which to change battery fill color (Default: 25)
   -s4 <Percent>   Percent at which to change battery fill color (Default: 50)
   -s5 <Percent>   Percent at which to change battery fill color (Default: 75)
   -bg <Colour>    Background color (Default: #d2dae4)
   -bs <Colour>    Battery border gradient start color (Defailt: #939494)
   -be <Colour>    Battery border gradient end color (Defailt: #2f2f2f)
   -ps <Colour>    Charing symbol gradient start color (Default: #939494)
   -pe <Colour>    Charing symbol gradient end color (Default: #2f2f2f)
   -fs1 <Colour>   Fill gradient start color when charge level > 0% (Defult: #e99494)
   -fs2 <Colour>   Fill gradient start color when charge level > s2 (Defult: #ebc984)
   -fs3 <Colour>   Fill gradient start color when charge level > s3 (Defult: #dcc200)
   -fs4 <Colour>   Fill gradient start color when charge level > s4 (Defult: #bcd788)
   -fs5 <Colour>   Fill gradient start color when charge level > s5 (Defult: #72ce46)
   -fe1 <Colour>   Fill gradient end color when charge level > 0% (Defult: #d63c3c)
   -fe2 <Colour>   Fill gradient end color when charge level > s2 (Defult: #d59a21)
   -fe3 <Colour>   Fill gradient end color when charge level > s3 (Defult: #cfb505)
   -fe4 <Colour>   Fill gradient end color when charge level > s4 (Defult: #7ea336)
   -fe5 <Colour>   Fill gradient end color when charge level > s5 (Defult: #218c22)
   -ba <Degrees>   Angle of the battery border gradient (Default: 90)
   -fa <Degrees>   Angle of the battery fill gradient (Default: 90)
   -pa <Degrees>   Angle of the charging symbol gradient (Default: 90)
   -h              Show this usage message

Example: wmHBattery -bg "#0000FF" -l -fa 45  


WindowMaker.
------------
In WindowMaker simply drag and drop the wmHBattery App on the WindowMaker Dock or Clip.





